CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Ground-Breaking - Some of the principals who took part in ground-breaking ceremonies Sunday for the new Bethel AME Church at the corner of Webster Ave. and Morgan St. are, left to right: Mmes. Katherine Blackwell, Georgia Johnson, Madelyn Jackson, Eloise Thompson, Alice Jefferson, Martha Wells, Bishop E.C. Hatcher, Sammy Wolk, Mayor David L. Lawrence, the Rev. G.L. Caddell of Steubenville, and Councilman Paul F. Jones. The pastor, the Rev. J.G. Harris, is not shown. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Katherine Blackwell, Georgia Johnson, Madelyn Jackson, Eloise Thompson, Alice Jefferson, Martha Wells, Bishop E.C. Hatcher, Sammy Wolk, Mayor David L. Lawrence, Rev. G.L. Caddell, and Councilman Paul F. Jones, standing on site of the new Bethel AME Church groundbreaking ceremony
